      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "BUTTE, Mont, June 1.-The\nButte union may withdraw from\nthe Western Federation of Miners\nas a result of the Withdrawing of\nPresident Frank OConnor and 9TH\ner delegates from the convention in\nDenver and the seating of Dele\ngates Lowney and Duffy. The mat\nter will come before the Butte\nunion on a referendum vote.\n\n\nIn statement made at Denver,\nthe boilers said that one reason\nfor their action was that Socialism\nwas spreading in the Western Fed\nGRAFTON of Miners and that there\nwere too many agitators in the\nfederation."
    }
  ]
